The paper deals with text-based analysis methods and proposes a method that uses sequence-to-sequence language models and generative adversarial networks to obfuscate author attributes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category of Computer Science (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper deals with privacy and anonymity, which suggests that it could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques such as neural networks and adversarial training suggests that the paper could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with text classification and attribute identification, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
